h4 Params

table.params-table
    tr
        td param
        td type
        td default
        td description
    tr
        td headers
        td Array[String]
        td ["A","B","C","D"]
        td Array with the names of each column
    tr
        td header_aliases
        td Object ({header: alias})
        td {}
        td A map to change the header's names on the table
    tr
        td table_class
        td String
        td "subtletable"
        td CSS class to apply to the table for styling
    tr
        td show_row_headers
        td Boolean
        td true
        td Show a column that indicates the row number
    tr
        td row_header_width
        td Number
        td 30
        td Row heades' column width (in pixels)
    tr
        td null_cell_text
        td String
        td ""
        td Value that should be displayed in case a cell has no value
    tr
        td allow_sort
        td Boolean
        td false
        td Let's the user sort the rows of the table by clicking the headers
    tr
        td insert_on_top
        td Boolean
        td false
        td Insert new rows on top
    tr
        td max_displayed_data
        td Number
        td 100
        td Max number of rows displayed
    tr
        td remove_old_data
        td Boolean
        td true
        td Remove old rows when the number of rows passes the limit (max_displayed_data)
    


//
h4 Update

p.
    Call the update method to add new rows to the table:

code
    | Subtle.Table.update(id, data)

p.
    For each row you insert, you need to specify a row id. You you also pass an empty string ("") as id
    and the data will be assigned an auto id.

p.
    The data argument on the update function is a dict {column: value}, where column is the name of the
    column as defined by the headers (Table.params.headers)

